\begin_layout Remark
Note that the notion of contextuality did not arise naturally, anywhere
 in the discussion.
 For completeness and clarification, observe that the Bohmian map 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{B}$
\end_inset

 is contextual, but the Bohmian prediction map 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 is non-contextual.
 Similarly the toy-model was also non-contextual.
\end_layout

