\begin_layout Proposition
Consider a product Hilbert space 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{H}_{A}\otimes\mathcal{H}_{B}$
\end_inset

, corresponding to two particles.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{H}_{A}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{H}_{B}$
\end_inset

 are discrete (correspond to spins say).
 Let mutually commuting observables 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{B}_{i}$
\end_inset

 be s.t.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{B}_{i}=\hat{\mathbb{I}}\otimes\hat{A}_{\text{B}i}$
\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{B}_{i}=\hat{A}_{\text{A}i}\otimes\hat{\mathbb{I}}$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $A_{\text{A}i}\in\mathcal{\hat{H}}_{A}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $A_{\text{B}i}\in\hat{\mathcal{H}}_{B}$
\end_inset

 are arbitrary observables.
 If locality is assumed, then a prediction map 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 and it's associated sequence map 
\begin_inset Formula $s$
\end_inset

 must be s.t.
 over these observables, sequential multiplicativity and multiplicativity
 become identical.
